                            <comment id="14472804" author="melix" created="Mon, 11 Jun 2012 07:19:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to amend the description, there are two issues in one, here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def foo = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date(), 1]
foo.add( 2 )
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we shouldn&apos;t throw any error. Second, this should throw an error, according to our flow typing implementation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def foo = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date()]
foo.add(1)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as well as&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def foo = [1]
foo = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Date()]
foo.add(1)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So basically, there&apos;s only one problem to be fixed here, which is the error with the type inference engine not recognizing that an integer may be added to the list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
